e:nowrap;text-align:left;'></td><td style='white-space:nowrap;text-align:left;'></td><td style='white-space:nowrap;text-align:left;'>DURING AIRCRAFT FLIGHT TESTING, THE ENGINE DID NOT RE-LIGHT FOLLOWING A COMMANDED INFLIGHT SHUT DOWN FOR RE-LIGHT TEST PURPOSES.  A DEAD STICK LANDING WAS ACCOMPLISHED.  THE FUEL CONTROL UNIT AND FLOW DIVIDER VALVE WERE SUBSEQUENTLY REPLACED.  P&WC WILL MONITOR INVESTIGATION OF THE INCIDENT AND WILL ADVISE OF ROOT CAUSE ONCE ESTABLISHED.</td></tr>
