t-align:left;'></td><td style='white-space:nowrap;text-align:left;'></td><td style='white-space:nowrap;text-align:left;'>(CAN) DURING CLIMB (6000 FT) THE ENGINE EXPERIENCED AN UNCOMMANDED POWER ROLL-BACK ACCOMPANIED BY ITT INCREASE, A LOUD BANG AND FLAMES EVIDENT FROM THE EXHAUST. THE PILOT SHUT THE ENGINE DOWN IN FLT, DECLARED AN EMERGENCY AND SUBSEQUENTLY LANDED ON A ROAD.  PWC WILL INVESTIGATE THE INCIDENT AND WILL SUPPLEMENT THIS REPORT TO PROVIDE ROOT CAUSE, ONCE DETERMINED.</td></tr>
